Come on. Put 'em up.

255
00:23:58,146 --> 00:23:59,206
(TUCKER GROANING)

256
00:24:20,005 --> 00:24:22,568
Well played, sir! Well played!

257
00:24:41,957 --> 00:24:43,429
More champagne, my lovely.

258
00:24:43,524 --> 00:24:44,746
Certainly, sir.

259
00:24:44,837 --> 00:24:46,988
Tucker' are you sure
you don't want a Shandy or something?

260
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:50,250
I've got to finish
this mission report, sir.

261
00:24:50,307 --> 00:24:52,842
And Pegasus wants to see us
as soon as we touchdown.

262
00:24:53,348 --> 00:24:55,629
The mission report?

263
00:24:55,846 --> 00:24:57,962
Oh, come on, Tucker. Live a little.

264
00:24:58,407 --> 00:25:01,615
You should learn to savour success.

265
00:25:01,671 --> 00:25:03,371
Work hard,

266
00:25:04,261 --> 00:25:07,207
play hard. Isn't that right...

267
00:25:08,389 --> 00:25:09,449
Barbara?

268
00:25:25,959 --> 00:25:28,393
Vortex is finished

269
00:25:29,128 --> 00:25:30,731
But better still,

270
00:25:30,791 --> 00:25:34,348
for years I believed what happened
in Mozambique was my fault.

271
00:25:35,269 --> 00:25:39,076
Now I realise it was only partly my fault.

272
00:25:39,687 --> 00:25:42,087
What did happen in Mozambique?

273
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:57,456
Excuse me, sir. We're coming in to land.
Can I stow that overhead for you?

274
00:25:57,512 --> 00:25:58,669
Certainly.

275
00:26:01,125 --> 00:26:04,202
Sir, I don't think he's a "Susan".

276
00:26:04,549 --> 00:26:07,463
But then you're not a linguist,
are you, Tucker'?

277
00:26:07,557 --> 00:26:11,599
It's not "Susan," it's "Shoooshan".

278
00:26:11,751 --> 00:26:15,950
From the Xinzhou region,
unless I'm very much mistaken.

279
00:26:16,806 --> 00:26:18,443
Thank you, Shoooshan.

280
00:26:32,487 --> 00:26:35,083
Foreign Secretary.

281
00:26:35,141 --> 00:26:38,188
I hope you've got something
for us, English.

282
00:26:38,279 --> 00:26:40,332
The Prime Minister is extremely concerned.

283
00:26:40,392 --> 00:26:42,441
[ENGLISH]:
He has every reason to be so.

284
00:26:42,758 --> 00:26:45,703
There is a plot
to kill the Chinese Premier.

285
00:26:45,798 --> 00:26:50,123
Masterminded by a group of
ruthless assassins called Vortex.

286
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,172
Good Lord.

287
00:26:52,233 --> 00:26:55,114
The danger, however, has been averted.

288
00:26:56,040 --> 00:26:59,278
Now that we have this.

289
00:27:05,287 --> 00:27:07,273
- English?
- Now, I know what you're going to say,

290
00:27:07,848 --> 00:27:10,726
it's a pretty small object

291
00:27:12,102 --> 00:27:16,107
Well, it's often the little things
that pack the biggest punch.

292
00:27:16,197 --> 00:27:19,525
After all, David killed Goliath
with a pebble.

293
00:27:19,526 --> 00:27:20,526
Sir.

294
00:27:20,553 --> 00:27:25,647
The mighty Vortex has been slain
by my possession of this small key.

295
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:51,312
Shoooshan.

296
00:27:52,522 --> 00:27:54,438
Susan.

297
00:27:58,088 --> 00:28:00,554
We got it, but Fisher talked.

298
00:28:03,114 --> 00:28:06,156
Understood. We'll deal with English.

299
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:12,240
You've got some more cleaning to do.

300
00:28:14,346 --> 00:28:16,498
Mummy, Mummy! Mr Rhubarb's here!

301
00:28:17,289 --> 00:28:21,358
Izzie, darling, why don't you
show him into the conservatory?

302
00:28:21,447 --> 00:28:22,571
I'll be with you in just a minute.

303
00:28:22,630 --> 00:28:25,067
Okay. Come on, come on, let's go!

304
00:28:25,161 --> 00:28:26,994
- [MR. RHUBARB]: Shall we?
- [IZZIE]: Hurry up, Mr. Rhubarb...

305
00:28:27,403 --> 00:28:31,439
Perhaps when you've found your key,
you'll give me a call.

306
00:28:31,529 --> 00:28:33,568
[PEGASUS]: I'm very sorry,
Foreign Secretary.

307
00:28:33,569 --> 00:28:35,369
I had hoped
to have more for you.

308
00:28:36,904 --> 00:28:38,640
[ENGLISH]: Oh, God.

309
00:28:40,582 --> 00:28:41,610
(GRUNTING)

310
00:28:46,249 --> 00:28:47,920
(VACUUM CLEANER WHIRRING)

311
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:11,221
Pegasus! I've got her!

312
00:29:11,882 --> 00:29:12,910
Come on, you witch.

313
00:29:13,003 --> 00:29:13,996
English?

314
00:29:14,090 --> 00:29:17,483
She was in Hong Kong! She's the killer!

315
00:29:17,610 --> 00:29:19,047
She's my mother!

316
00:29:21,449 --> 00:29:22,639
Couldn't she be both?

317
00:29:25,449 --> 00:29:26,443
(EXCLAIMS)

318
00:29:27,051 --> 00:29:29,332
Mummy, Mummy, are you all right?

319
00:29:30,253 --> 00:29:32,203
Let me get you a cup of tea.

320
00:29:35,081 --> 00:29:37,614
- You'll be fine, Mummy.
- Who was that man?

321
00:29:38,153 --> 00:29:42,291
Yeah, I think a cup of tea,
that's what's required.

322
00:29:47,367 --> 00:29:50,349
Pegasus, I am truly, truly sorry.

323
00:29:50,444 --> 00:29:53,171
Don't apologise to me. Apologise to her.

324
00:30:04,395 --> 00:30:09,778
I cannot apologise enough, Mrs Pegasus.

325
00:30:10,955 --> 00:30:14,260
It was a simple case of mistaken identity,
I'm afraid.

326
00:30:14,955 --> 00:30:16,339
Now, I completely understand

327
00:30:16,392 --> 00:30:18,262
how upset you are,
but I was hoping perhaps...

328
00:30:24,011 --> 00:30:25,037
[TUCKER]: Sir!

329
00:30:25,355 --> 00:30:29,554
Tucker! That's her!
It's the killer from Hong Kong!

330
00:30:29,642 --> 00:30:32,271
- No, it's not her, sir.
- It is! This time it's really her!

331
00:30:32,362 --> 00:30:35,220
- It's not her, sir!
- Yes, it is!

332
00:30:42,413 --> 00:30:43,699
[ENGLISH]: Make way!

333
00:30:44,171 --> 00:30:45,459
Sir.

334
00:30:46,476 --> 00:30:48,494
You murderous crone!

335
00:30:50,571 --> 00:30:52,974
[IZZIE]: Granny!
What's he doing?

336
00:30:53,675 --> 00:30:54,933
[ENGLISH]: Take that!
And that!

337
00:30:56,651 --> 00:30:58,418
[IZZIE]: Hey! Stop it.

338
00:30:59,051 --> 00:31:00,045
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

339
00:31:00,813 --> 00:31:01,803
English!

340
00:31:02,763 --> 00:31:05,146
I've got her this time, Pegasus!

341
00:31:05,934 --> 00:31:09,327
This is the witch who works for Vortex!

342
00:31:09,454 --> 00:31:11,732
Want any more' you old hag?

343
00:31:11,851 --> 00:31:13,520
- English!
- Granny!

344
00:31:23,694 --> 00:31:26,189
You humiliate me
in front of the Foreign Secretary,

345
00:31:26,282 --> 00:31:29,610
you lose our only lead on Vortex,
and then you try and kill my mother!

346
00:31:30,636 --> 00:31:31,857
Twice!

347
00:31:32,814 --> 00:31:36,205
Pegasus, we have another lead.
Vortex was in Mozambique!

348
00:31:36,335 --> 00:31:39,410
They were responsible
for the death of President Chambal!

349
00:31:39,532 --> 00:31:43,373
No! You were responsible
for the death of President Chambal.

350
00:31:47,053 --> 00:31:48,045
(CHILDREN LAUGH)

351
00:31:54,603 --> 00:31:57,485
Well, you certainly gave Mr Rhubarb
a run for his money.

352
00:31:59,276 --> 00:32:03,698
Still, at least we know Vortex
was in Mozambique.

353
00:32:05,296 --> 00:32:06,516
When you told Pegasus,

354
00:32:06,605 --> 00:32:09,681
you displayed all four indicators
of someone telling the truth.

355
00:32:17,614 --> 00:32:19,253
[SUMNER]: This is a facial action
coding system.

356
00:32:20,814 --> 00:32:23,247
Its high-speed cameras
record microexpressions,

357
00:32:23,372 --> 00:32:24,846
invisible to the naked eye.

358
00:32:24,973 --> 00:32:27,088
It detects what we call emotional leakage.

359
00:32:27,214 --> 00:32:30,934
Ms. Sumner, I'm a trained agent.
I don't "leak".

360
00:32:31,310 --> 00:32:33,940
I want to take you back to Mozambique.

361
00:32:34,127 --> 00:32:35,154
(BEEPING)

362
00:32:35,247 --> 00:32:36,915
Is that really necessary?

363
00:32:39,150 --> 00:32:40,338
[SUMNER]: Take a look at this.

364
00:32:42,030 --> 00:32:44,112
<i>[SUMNER ON TV]:
I want to take you back to Mozambique.</i>

365
00:32:46,831 --> 00:32:48,402
[SUMNER]: There.

366
00:32:48,495 --> 00:32:50,577
Could we call that leakage?

367
00:32:50,892 --> 00:32:55,059
Now, play ball.
I'm taking a risk being here after hours.

368
00:32:55,629 --> 00:32:58,775
If Vortex was in Mozambique,
perhaps you saw something.

369
00:32:58,897 --> 00:33:01,655
I'm going to take you back there
using hypnosis.

370
00:33:01,776 --> 00:33:05,077
Oh, please.
Spare me the new age mumbo jumbo.

371
00:33:05,165 --> 00:33:08,048
Mr English' please. I'm a professional.

372
00:33:08,174 --> 00:33:09,527
I'm not going to just snap my fingers

373
00:33:09,613 --> 00:33:13,303
and make you say the first thing
that comes into your head.

374
00:33:13,389 --> 00:33:14,831
Plump pillows.

375
00:33:14,927 --> 00:33:16,533
Excuse me?

376
00:33:16,655 --> 00:33:20,242
Brilliant mind. Beautiful face.

377
00:33:20,333 --> 00:33:21,623
Incredible.

378
00:33:22,254 --> 00:33:25,135
And completely out of my league.

379
00:33:27,471 --> 00:33:28,758
Mmm.

380
00:33:30,736 --> 00:33:33,975
I'd like to take you back to Mozambique.

381
00:33:38,734 --> 00:33:41,462
Tell me what's happening, Johnny.
Where are you?

382
00:33:42,513 --> 00:33:45,238
<i>[ENGLISH]: President Chambal's
inauguration day.</i>

383
00:33:45,873 --> 00:33:48,499
<i>[SUMNER]:
Yes, you're head of security.</i>

384
00:33:51,055 --> 00:33:53,009
<i>[ENGLISH]: Everything's going perfectly.</i>

385
00:33:53,133 --> 00:33:55,222
<i>Today we climb the mountain!</i>

386
00:33:55,377 --> 00:33:57,078
[MADELEINE WHISPERING]:
Agent English.

387
00:33:59,409 --> 00:34:02,733
<i>[CHAMBAL]: The people have spoken,
and the message is clear.</i>

388
00:34:04,048 --> 00:34:06,098
<i>A future of peace and prosperity!</i>

389
00:34:06,190 --> 00:34:09,236
The backup electrical supply has been cut.

390
00:34:11,376 --> 00:34:14,289
No, it hasn't. It's been turned off.

391
00:34:16,173 --> 00:34:18,129
Do you know how to turn it on?

392
00:34:19,886 --> 00:34:21,941
I should be getting back.

393
00:34:23,219 --> 00:34:26,099
Well, operations like this
are always difficult.

394
00:34:26,193 --> 00:34:28,179
But it's very satisfying
when you get a result.

395
00:34:28,274 --> 00:34:30,965
The President couldn't be in safer hands.

396
00:34:31,055 --> 00:34:33,489
<i>The future belongs to Mozambique!</i>

397
00:34:34,414 --> 00:34:35,539
<i>Thank you.</i>

398
00:34:35,791 --> 00:34:36,916
- (GUNSHOTS)
- (PEOPLE SCREAMING)

399
00:34:37,008 --> 00:34:39,223
The fireworks have begun.

400
00:34:40,178 --> 00:34:42,293
The sound of freedom and celebration.

401
00:34:44,046 --> 00:34:45,488
(CLAMOURING)

402
00:34:49,616 --> 00:34:54,297
Easy, Johnny. Easy. Go back.
Before the Jacuzzi, what did you see?

403
00:34:59,696 --> 00:35:01,137
[ENGLISH]: Yes.

404
00:35:02,129 --> 00:35:03,419
Fisher.

405
00:35:05,168 --> 00:35:07,386
On the terrace with two others.

406
00:35:07,473 --> 00:35:11,378
[SUMNER]: Yes. All 3 members of Vortex
were there that day.

407
00:35:11,471 --> 00:35:14,678
Who can you see?
Who can you see, Johnny?

408
00:35:17,391 --> 00:35:20,221
<i>[ENGLISH]: Artem Karlenko.</i>

409
00:35:23,379 --> 00:35:25,778
<i>[PEGASUS]:
Artem Karlenko, double agent.</i>

410
00:35:25,874 --> 00:35:28,502
<i>Recruited by MI7 in Moscow.</i>

411
00:35:28,752 --> 00:35:31,700
<i>Retired after his penchant for
killing people threatened his cover.</i>

412
00:35:32,592 --> 00:35:34,581
Five years ago, he turned up here

413
00:35:35,217 --> 00:35:37,137
as Sergei Pudovkin.

414
00:35:37,233 --> 00:35:38,935
Rich, very rich.

415
00:35:39,059 --> 00:35:41,042
A member of the exclusive
Oakwood Golf Club,

416
00:35:41,136 --> 00:35:42,459
<i>which is where you'll be meeting him.</i>

417
00:35:42,576 --> 00:35:45,139
He's in a match play competition, sir.

418
00:35:45,230 --> 00:35:47,067
I'm making you his opponent for the day.

419
00:35:50,482 --> 00:35:53,144
Done it, sir.
You're booked in as Mr Peter Adams.

420
00:35:55,631 --> 00:35:57,052
Thank you, Tucker.

421
00:35:58,163 --> 00:36:02,744
If Karlenko is Vortex,
I want you to bring him in. Alive.

422
00:36:27,155 --> 00:36:29,074
Mr Pussykin?

423
00:36:29,458 --> 00:36:33,049
Pudovkin. And you must be Mr

424
00:36:35,379 --> 00:36:36,335
Um...

425
00:36:37,072 --> 00:36:38,579
Adams.

426
00:36:38,897 --> 00:36:41,299
Beautiful car, Mr Adams.

427
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,124
Ah, the Royce.

428
00:36:43,218 --> 00:36:44,246
<i>[AUTOMATED VOICE]: Ready, sir.</i>

429
00:36:44,980 --> 00:36:46,103
Thank you.

430
00:36:46,739 --> 00:36:48,182
Shall we?

431
00:36:48,819 --> 00:36:49,943
Let's go.

432
00:36:50,004 --> 00:36:51,387
<i>[AUTOMATED VOICE]:
Command accepted.</i>

433
00:36:52,722 --> 00:36:55,930
So, what line of business are you in,
Mr Adams?

434
00:36:56,021 --> 00:36:57,145
Pudovkin.

435
00:36:58,002 --> 00:37:00,569
Sorry. Yes, I'm Mr Adams, and you're Mr...

436
00:37:00,659 --> 00:37:03,061
Whoever you said you were

437
00:37:03,156 --> 00:37:04,986
- Well...
- Stop!

438
00:37:07,699 --> 00:37:10,742
Sorry, I thought I had forgotten something.

439
00:37:36,082 --> 00:37:37,467
Glove, sir'?

440
00:37:38,898 --> 00:37:40,667
I may not know much about golf, Tucker,

441
00:37:40,726 --> 00:37:43,156
but I know how to hold the bat.

442
00:38:08,565 --> 00:38:09,951
Shot, sir.

443
00:38:23,636 --> 00:38:26,966
[ENGLISH]: So, what line of business
are you in, Mr Puddykin?

444
00:38:27,062 --> 00:38:30,004
[KARLENKO]: I made my money
in the removals business.

445
00:38:32,083 --> 00:38:36,350
A friend of mine had shares
in a removals business. Titus Fisher.

446
00:38:36,404 --> 00:38:39,002
You haven't come across him at all?

447
00:38:39,925 --> 00:38:43,005
I warn you, Mr Adams,
not to stray into the rough.

448
00:38:43,477 --> 00:38:45,787
You get in there, you might never come out.

449
00:38:45,844 --> 00:38:47,863
I'll bear that in mind, Mr Puddykin.

450
00:38:47,958 --> 00:38:50,652
Pudovkin. Please.

451
00:38:55,543 --> 00:38:56,502
(BALL HITS)

452
00:38:56,663 --> 00:38:57,688
(MAN GRUNTS)

453
00:39:03,924 --> 00:39:05,149
Shot!

454
00:39:05,973 --> 00:39:08,506
As was my friend Fisher, actually.

455
00:39:09,687 --> 00:39:11,325
In the back.

456
00:39:13,394 --> 00:39:15,317
By his cleaner, of all people.

457
00:39:22,103 --> 00:39:24,220
But they didn't take much.

458
00:39:24,855 --> 00:39:25,879
Just a key

459
00:39:33,494 --> 00:39:35,133
Break, left to right, I think.

460
00:39:35,223 --> 00:39:36,380
Thank you.

461
00:39:36,725 --> 00:39:37,720
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

462
00:39:55,862 --> 00:39:56,854
(GRUNTS)

463
00:39:58,900 --> 00:40:00,341
(STAMMERING) In the trees.

464
00:40:04,120 --> 00:40:05,536
Come on.

465
00:40:05,879 --> 00:40:07,386
(KARLENKO MOANING)

466
00:40:07,447 --> 00:40:09,793
- Oh, my God.
- He can't die. He mustn't die.

467
00:40:09,845 --> 00:40:11,798
[ENGLISH]: Let's get him out of here.
Come on! Come on.

468
00:40:15,927 --> 00:40:16,987
[TUCKER]:
He's not looking good, sir.

469
00:40:18,135 --> 00:40:21,562
We're getting you to a doctor.
You'll be fine.

470
00:40:23,316 --> 00:40:24,889
You do know how to fly these, sir?

471
00:40:24,982 --> 00:40:27,132
- It was part of basic training.
- Good.

472
00:40:27,222 --> 00:40:28,989
It's just like riding a bike.

473
00:40:30,904 --> 00:40:32,377
(TUCKER YELLING)

474
00:40:34,968 --> 00:40:37,464
Yes. It's all coming back to me.

475
00:40:38,261 --> 00:40:39,965
(TUCKER EXCLAIMING)

476
00:40:58,361 --> 00:41:02,204
This is helicopter
Golf Hotel Zulu Zulu Tango.

477
00:41:02,298 --> 00:41:05,567
We have a casualty on board.
Request guidance to nearest hospital.

478
00:41:05,655 --> 00:41:06,907
<i>[MAN ON RADIO]:
Where's your exact location?</i>

479
00:41:06,965 --> 00:41:08,286
Our location?
Location?

480
00:41:08,886 --> 00:41:12,542
She shot out the navigation system.
Hang on.

481
00:41:19,317 --> 00:41:20,345
(CAR HONKING)

482
00:41:22,648 --> 00:41:25,373
- Runstock.
- Our location is Runstock.

483
00:41:25,463 --> 00:41:26,523
<i>[MAN ON RADIO]:
What is your altitude?</i>

484
00:41:26,617 --> 00:41:28,417
What's our altitude?

485
00:41:30,167 --> 00:41:32,123
About 18 inches.

486
00:41:32,729 --> 00:41:35,105
Hello? Hello?

487
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:39,589
Sorry. I'll just move.

488
00:41:41,494 --> 00:41:43,066
[TUCKER]: What now, sir'?

489
00:41:43,128 --> 00:41:46,589
[ENGLISH]: We'll have to stick to the road.
Let's follow the 1328.

490
00:41:46,650 --> 00:41:48,121
There's bound to be a hospital in Dingham.

491
00:41:54,006 --> 00:41:55,068
(KARLENKO GROANING)

492
00:41:55,129 --> 00:41:56,669
Look after him, Tucker. Look after him.

493
00:42:00,379 --> 00:42:01,371
(CAR HONKING)

494
00:42:03,255 --> 00:42:05,950
- I think we're losing him, sir.
- We can't lose him, Tucker.

495
00:42:06,007 --> 00:42:09,499
He's our only lead. Try something else.

496
00:42:14,906 --> 00:42:18,265
<i>[TUCKER SINGING]:
Don't give up on us, baby</i>

497
00:42:18,328 --> 00:42:24,091
<i>Lord knows we've come this far</i>

498
00:42:24,699 --> 00:42:26,269
(VOCALISING)

499
00:42:28,828 --> 00:42:34,814
<i>[BOTH SINGING]: We are
The angel and the dreamer</i>

500
00:42:35,226 --> 00:42:36,930
(BOTH VOCALISING)

501
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:40,897
<i>Don'! give up on us, I know</i>

502
00:42:41,467 --> 00:42:44,826
<i>We could still come through</i>

503
00:42:53,018 --> 00:42:54,752
(MEN SCREAMING)

504
00:43:00,054 --> 00:43:02,972
[TUCKER]: Look, sir!
Follow that ambulance!

505
00:43:03,066 --> 00:43:04,507
Good idea.

506
00:43:14,681 --> 00:43:16,383
[TUCKER]: Sir.
Sir, quickly.

507
00:43:19,803 --> 00:43:22,149
Karlenko. Karlenko!

508
00:43:29,049 --> 00:43:30,687
The second key.

509
00:43:32,189 --> 00:43:36,901
Vortex is KGB...

510
00:43:37,722 --> 00:43:40,190
- Yes.
- CIA.

511
00:43:43,288 --> 00:43:45,536
Yes? Yes?

512
00:43:49,853 --> 00:43:51,270
MI7.

513
00:43:59,547 --> 00:44:04,293
Unbelievable. A vole in MI7.

514
00:44:06,813 --> 00:44:08,545
A mole, sir.

515
00:44:09,464 --> 00:44:10,753
What?

516
00:44:11,161 --> 00:44:13,247
There's a mole in MI7.

517
00:44:14,362 --> 00:44:16,352
There's a mole and a vole?

518
00:44:16,926 --> 00:44:20,229
No, sir. There's a mole, not a vole.

519
00:44:20,926 --> 00:44:23,268
Well, I disagree. There's certainly a vole.

520
00:44:23,322 --> 00:44:25,025
I mean, we know that much.

521
00:44:25,081 --> 00:44:28,542
But what you're saying is
there might be a mole as well.

522
00:44:29,181 --> 00:44:30,204
(MOBILE PHONE CHIMES)

523
00:44:30,298 --> 00:44:31,455
Pegasus.

524
00:44:32,859 --> 00:44:36,418
There's a meeting at MI7
with the Prime Minister.

525
00:44:41,785 --> 00:44:45,412
And here again, eyes down
and to the left, indicating dissent.

526
00:44:45,501 --> 00:44:47,651
With Xiang Ping, it's all about the eyes.

527
00:44:47,741 --> 00:44:50,339
Thank you, Ms. Sumner. If the talks
go ahead, I'd like you with us.

528
00:44:51,866 --> 00:44:53,469
Yes, Prime Minister.

529
00:44:54,746 --> 00:44:56,285
Good evening, gentlemen.

530
00:44:56,379 --> 00:44:57,734
- Mr English.
- Ms Sumner.

531
00:45:00,381 --> 00:45:01,538
Right.

532
00:45:02,813 --> 00:45:06,946
So when is the Prime Minister
going to grace us with his presence?

533
00:45:07,292 --> 00:45:08,995
I'm the Prime Minister.

534
00:45:09,085 --> 00:45:10,949
(SNORTS) Yeah, you wish.

535
00:45:21,177 --> 00:45:23,330
All right. So we're all here.

536
00:45:24,253 --> 00:45:25,245
(CLEARING THROAT)

537
00:45:25,854 --> 00:45:29,639
These talks with China
are of paramount importance.

538
00:45:29,692 --> 00:45:30,979
Rogue slates in Southeast Asia

539
00:45:31,071 --> 00:45:33,251
have begun secretly to develop
nuclear weapons.

540
00:45:33,341 --> 00:45:36,100
It is vital that we get China onside.

541
00:45:36,188 --> 00:45:38,913
Traditionally, China has been
impervious to our concerns,

542
00:45:38,972 --> 00:45:41,157
but I believe Xiang Ping,
given the opportunity,

543
00:45:41,213 --> 00:45:44,706
can and will help defuse this situation.

544
00:45:44,829 --> 00:45:47,144
[FOREIGN SECRETARY]: Well,
with his pro-West stance,

545
00:45:47,231 --> 00:45:48,930
it certainly offers an opportunity,

546
00:45:49,020 --> 00:45:52,829
but the talks can't go ahead
unless we can guarantee his safety.

547
00:45:52,893 --> 00:45:54,847
I believe, with the correct security,
that we can.

548
00:45:54,940 --> 00:45:57,888
If Vortex is operational
it's just too dangerous

549
00:45:57,982 --> 00:46:00,743
[FOREIGN SECRETARY]:
I'm inclined to agree, Prime Minister.

550
00:46:02,971 --> 00:46:04,225
[AMBROSE]: There is a way.

551
00:46:05,214 --> 00:46:08,389
The Swiss are willing to lend us
Le Bastion.

552
00:46:08,508 --> 00:46:10,594
That's their government fortress
in the Alps.

553
00:46:10,975 --> 00:46:15,296
It's a stunning example of
architectural engineering at altitude,

554
00:46:15,391 --> 00:46:18,115
and completely impregnable.

555
00:46:18,171 --> 00:46:21,502
I mean, that should solve
all our security issues.

556
00:46:22,270 --> 00:46:24,035
Then the talks go ahead.

557
00:46:24,091 --> 00:46:25,992
Pamela, I hope you've brushed up
on your Mandarin.

558
00:46:26,109 --> 00:46:29,733
I'd like you in the room with me,
and your best man on security.

559
00:46:29,823 --> 00:46:31,588
Yes, Prime Minister.

560
00:46:33,468 --> 00:46:35,715
Where are we on Vortex?

561
00:46:36,828 --> 00:46:37,858
English?

562
00:46:38,463 --> 00:46:43,265
Vortex is three men.
Fisher was one, Karlenko was another.

563
00:46:43,392 --> 00:46:47,109
Karlenko was killed today
on the orders of the third.

564
00:46:48,253 --> 00:46:49,672
[PEGASUS]: Any leads?

565
00:46:49,789 --> 00:46:51,874
Yes, but I need time.

566
00:46:51,933 --> 00:46:53,703
[PEGASUS]:
We do not have time.

567
00:46:53,791 --> 00:46:57,794
We need to know the identity
of the third person in Vortex.

568
00:47:02,781 --> 00:47:04,517
Give me 24 hours.

569
00:47:15,775 --> 00:47:17,063
Another bottle of Romaine-Conti?

570
00:47:17,950 --> 00:47:19,784
Of course.
And would you like to choose dessert?

571
00:47:19,871 --> 00:47:21,823
Yes. You.

572
00:47:23,582 --> 00:47:25,669
And bring two spoons.

573
00:47:25,792 --> 00:47:27,428
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

574
00:47:30,270 --> 00:47:31,937
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

575
00:47:32,349 --> 00:47:33,953
Cheers.

576
00:47:36,032 --> 00:47:39,239
So, come on, Johnny,
what was it you wanted to ask me'?

577
00:47:43,583 --> 00:47:47,782
Simon, do you know what this is?

578
00:47:51,393 --> 00:47:53,194
Some sort of key?

579
00:47:53,314 --> 00:47:58,593
Karlenko and Fisher both had one,
and they were both killed for them.

580
00:47:59,454 --> 00:48:03,658
Well, I'll give it to the boys
at the lab and see...

581
00:48:03,744 --> 00:48:09,831
Karlenko told me that the third man
in Vortex is in MI7.

582
00:48:16,095 --> 00:48:19,587
And you believed him?

583
00:48:20,224 --> 00:48:26,462
Simon, I have to ask you a question,
face to face.

584
00:48:28,669 --> 00:48:32,841
Do you have any idea who it might be?

585
00:48:35,425 --> 00:48:38,752
Johnny, I thought
you were about to accuse me.

586
00:48:38,815 --> 00:48:40,200
No! I mean, honestly.

587
00:48:40,256 --> 00:48:41,314
(BOTH LAUGHING)

588
00:48:41,375 --> 00:48:44,039
- What?
- Simon Ambrose, the evil mastermind!

589
00:48:44,097 --> 00:48:45,961
- Don't. Stop it-
- The traitor in our midst!

590
00:48:46,016 --> 00:48:47,401
You! You!

591
00:48:49,024 --> 00:48:50,630
Simon, you are so funny.

592
00:48:51,967 --> 00:48:53,319
(GURGLING) Hysterical.

593
00:48:54,591 --> 00:48:55,749
Oh, dear.

594
00:48:55,870 --> 00:48:56,830
(MOBILE PHONE BEEPS)

595
00:48:59,169 --> 00:49:01,670
Would you excuse me
for one moment, Simon?

596
00:49:15,071 --> 00:49:17,059
- Sir.
- Tucker, can'! this wait?

597
00:49:17,153 --> 00:49:18,791
Sir, it's Ambrose.

598
00:49:19,395 --> 00:49:21,062
Yes, I know it's Ambrose.
I'm having dinner with him.

599
00:49:21,151 --> 00:49:23,717
No, he's the third man in Vortex.

600
00:49:25,345 --> 00:49:27,243
Simon Ambrose?

601
00:49:28,546 --> 00:49:30,596
He went to Eton.

602
00:49:30,914 --> 00:49:31,875
(DOOR OPENS)

603
00:49:32,834 --> 00:49:34,058
Simon.

604
00:49:34,148 --> 00:49:35,236
Leave it.

605
00:49:38,207 --> 00:49:39,235
- What are you...
- Move.

606
00:49:39,329 --> 00:49:41,348
- All right, all right.
- Come on, move.

607
00:49:41,474 --> 00:49:43,080
Tucker.

608
00:49:43,905 --> 00:49:47,264
- You said you never knew Karlenko.
- That's right.

609
00:49:47,392 --> 00:49:49,824
Then how do you explain these?

610
00:49:50,433 --> 00:49:54,274
I hacked into Karlenko's computer.
You and him in Mozambique?

611
00:50:21,248 --> 00:50:24,045
Sometimes I have trouble myself, old boy.

612
00:50:41,956 --> 00:50:43,723
You're Vortex!
You're the third man in Vortex!

613
00:50:43,810 --> 00:50:44,934
Tucker, this is ridiculous.

614
00:50:45,026 --> 00:50:46,050
(URINATING)

615
00:50:46,145 --> 00:50:47,980
Sorry, I'll be with you in just a tick.

616
00:50:48,291 --> 00:50:49,960
It's true, I was in Mozambique.

617
00:50:50,850 --> 00:50:52,071
What?

618
00:50:52,517 --> 00:50:55,724
I was there because of Patch Quartermain.

619
00:50:55,778 --> 00:50:59,465
Patch? Sorry, I'll just be one second.

620
00:50:59,552 --> 00:51:02,317
He's the man you're after.

621
00:51:02,787 --> 00:51:04,837
- You're bluffing!
- Sorry.

622
00:51:04,898 --> 00:51:08,106
I work for a secret organisation inside MI7

623
00:51:08,195 --> 00:51:10,793
set up specifically to bring him in.

624
00:51:11,621 --> 00:51:13,518
A secret Secret Service?

625
00:51:13,635 --> 00:51:15,915
Yeah? What's it called?

626
00:51:16,515 --> 00:51:18,433
What's it called?

627
00:51:20,193 --> 00:51:21,485
Armitage.

628
00:51:21,700 --> 00:51:25,160
A secret secret secret service
called Armitage?

629
00:51:25,541 --> 00:51:27,753
We answer only to the PM.

630
00:51:29,985 --> 00:51:32,202
It's extraordinary, Simon...

631
00:51:32,708 --> 00:51:33,996
[AMBROSE]: Indeed, it is.

632
00:51:34,115 --> 00:51:37,192
That you'd think for one moment...

633
00:51:37,315 --> 00:51:42,180
that I would fall for
such a steaming pile of old baloney.

634
00:51:42,273 --> 00:51:45,385
Well done, Tucker.
You're not Spy of the Month for nothing.

635
00:51:45,473 --> 00:51:48,552
- Thank you, sir.
- Here, let me take that.

636
00:51:48,674 --> 00:51:49,832
Now go home.

637
00:51:50,919 --> 00:51:53,744
- What?
- You're the one talking baloney.

638
00:51:53,829 --> 00:51:56,522
You're in way over your head, boy.
Now run along.

639
00:51:56,580 --> 00:51:59,908
No! I won't go, sir. He's lying.

640
00:52:00,036 --> 00:52:03,178
You've let me down,
you've let the Service down

641
00:52:03,268 --> 00:52:05,253
and, frankly,
I think you've let yourself down.

642
00:52:05,348 --> 00:52:07,914
- But I...
- Now get out!

643
00:52:12,579 --> 00:52:17,514
Patch Quartermain, of all people.
Blowing his own legs off?

644
00:52:17,638 --> 00:52:20,518
Now that's what I call deep cover.

645
00:52:20,580 --> 00:52:22,349
And to think how much I admired him.

646
00:52:22,436 --> 00:52:23,465
He hates you.

647
00:52:24,388 --> 00:52:26,602
- Really?
- He always has.

648
00:52:26,659 --> 00:52:29,833
He thinks you're a moron
with no place in MI7,

649
00:52:29,957 --> 00:52:34,344
a jumped-up grammar school nobody
That's why he tried to destroy you.

650
00:52:36,263 --> 00:52:39,979
Now, Johnny,
just because he ruined your life,

651
00:52:40,069 --> 00:52:42,796
that's no reason for you to go rogue
and take him down on your own.

652
00:52:45,348 --> 00:52:48,841
God forbid I should put a crazy idea
like that in your head.

653
00:52:50,983 --> 00:52:52,682
Good night, Simon.

654
00:52:53,699 --> 00:52:57,990
Johnny, that key you showed me.
We might need it to bring him in.

655
00:53:03,716 --> 00:53:06,031
- Thank you.
- You're welcome, sir.

656
00:53:07,588 --> 00:53:08,909
Silly tit.

657
00:53:13,637 --> 00:53:14,795
Bingo.

658
00:53:17,318 --> 00:53:19,239
- Arrange a meeting with our client
- [MADELEINE]: Of course.

659
00:53:32,104 --> 00:53:33,489
Pegasus.

660
00:53:34,630 --> 00:53:36,363
We have the third man.

661
00:53:38,949 --> 00:53:40,847
It's Johnny English.

662
00:53:51,235 --> 00:53:52,678
[ENGLISH]: Hello, Patch.

663
00:53:53,318 --> 00:53:55,306
Looking for forgiveness?

664
00:53:57,477 --> 00:54:02,130
It's all over for you now, English.
It's the end of the line.

665
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:05,096
Yes, you'd like that, wouldn't you, Patch?

666
00:54:05,189 --> 00:54:09,324
After all, I'm just a jumped-up
grammar school nobody, aren't I?

667
00:54:09,830 --> 00:54:11,272
(CHUCKLING) What are you talking about?

668
00:54:12,519 --> 00:54:17,679
I know that you are the third man
in Vortex.

669
00:54:21,157 --> 00:54:23,755
No, Johnny. You are.

670
00:54:24,901 --> 00:54:26,288
No, you are.

671
00:54:26,344 --> 00:54:28,045
No. You are!

672
00:54:29,799 --> 00:54:31,880
Standby, all agents.

673
00:54:31,940 --> 00:54:34,124
And it all ends here.

674
00:54:38,953 --> 00:54:40,078
<i>[PEGASUS]: Take him.</i>

675
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:43,560
(SILENCED GUNSHOT)

676
00:54:43,625 --> 00:54:44,682
(METALLIC CLANGING)

677
00:54:55,943 --> 00:54:57,004
(GRUNTS)

678
00:55:21,640 --> 00:55:22,928
Johnny.

679
00:55:34,503 --> 00:55:35,597
[WOMAN]: Hey! Watch it!

680
00:55:38,441 --> 00:55:40,395
Got him! Move! Move!

681
00:55:41,962 --> 00:55:43,433
Don't lose him. Go, go!

682
00:55:43,592 --> 00:55:44,682
Halt!

683
00:55:44,839 --> 00:55:45,799
(CAR HONKING)

684
00:55:57,992 --> 00:56:00,903
Heading west into Vine Street.
Mobilise all vehicles.

685
00:56:36,521 --> 00:56:37,483
Idiot!

686
00:56:45,227 --> 00:56:47,953
You've lost him! I don't believe it.

687
00:57:01,356 --> 00:57:03,732
Oi! Who do you think you are?

688
00:57:06,796 --> 00:57:07,786
(ALL GASPING)

689
00:57:39,915 --> 00:57:42,031
Gotcha.

690
00:58:00,043 --> 00:58:01,364
(SIRENS BLARING)

691
00:58:10,923 --> 00:58:13,969
<i>[AGENT]: Agent English, pull over!
Pullover!</i>

692
00:58:39,946 --> 00:58:41,006
[MAN]: Stop it!

693
00:58:44,876 --> 00:58:46,000
[AGENT]: Get after him.

694
00:58:52,843 --> 00:58:54,351
(POP MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

695
00:59:03,403 --> 00:59:04,395
(SCREAMS)

696
00:59:04,523 --> 00:59:07,566
Kate, Kate, I'm not Vortex.
I've been framed.

697
00:59:08,588 --> 00:59:10,837
You must believe me.

698
00:59:36,589 --> 00:59:37,842
<i>[CHI HANLY]: How will it be done?</i>

699
00:59:41,743 --> 00:59:45,579
Same as in Mozambique.
One person, apparently working alone.

700
00:59:46,990 --> 00:59:48,276
Who have you chosen?

701
00:59:48,908 --> 00:59:50,449
Leave that with me.

702
00:59:53,229 --> 00:59:58,028
My account in Zurich.
500 million US dollars, as agreed.

703
01:00:13,036 --> 01:00:14,357
You've been out for hours

704
01:00:25,165 --> 01:00:26,191
(GRUNTS)

705
01:00:26,284 --> 01:00:28,850
Well, you're lucky
it was just a flesh wound.

706
01:00:28,909 --> 01:00:30,509
Now, look,
I'm going to Switzerland tonight,

707
01:00:30,510 --> 01:00:32,410
but you can stay here
while I'm gone.

708
01:00:33,806 --> 01:00:34,830
Mmm-hmm. Mmm-hmm.

709
01:00:34,925 --> 01:00:39,031
I've been going through the news footage
from the night Chambal was killed.

710
01:00:39,948 --> 01:00:41,902
And there's something not right.

711
01:00:41,996 --> 01:00:44,079
Seconds after President Chambal was shot,

712
01:00:44,142 --> 01:00:46,389
the assassin collapses and dies.

713
01:00:46,479 --> 01:00:49,590
And the autopsy says heart failure.

714
01:00:49,679 --> 01:00:54,512
But, if you go through
the classified CCTV footage...

715
01:00:55,884 --> 01:00:57,107
(CLATTERING)

716
01:00:57,740 --> 01:00:59,248
You all right?

717
01:00:59,756 --> 01:01:01,327
Yeah, fine.

718
01:01:02,319 --> 01:01:04,307
Take a look at this.

719
01:01:04,943 --> 01:01:10,353
Fifteen minutes before
the assassination, look, he's manic.

720
01:01:10,444 --> 01:01:13,009
He's completely lost control of his body

721
01:01:13,069 --> 01:01:15,952
And then, suddenly, catatonic.

722
01:01:18,351 --> 01:01:19,922
Here, wait.

723
01:01:21,198 --> 01:01:22,354
There.

724
01:01:22,763 --> 01:01:24,883
Someone was talking to him.

725
01:01:28,527 --> 01:01:32,216
I don't think he had any idea
what he was doing.

726
01:01:32,271 --> 01:01:34,673
I think Vortex's secret weapon...

727
01:01:35,407 --> 01:01:38,516
Is a mind control drug.

728
01:01:38,606 --> 01:01:40,885
And only one fits the symptoms.

729
01:01:43,184 --> 01:01:46,294
Timox... Timoxylin Bubby...

730
01:01:46,350 --> 01:01:48,152
[SUMNER]: Timoxeline Barbebutenol.

731
01:01:48,688 --> 01:01:51,893
The CIA ordered its destruction
10 years ago.

732
01:01:51,950 --> 01:01:55,258
And the agent in charge of its disposal...

733
01:01:56,208 --> 01:01:57,909
[ENGLISH]: Titus Fisher.

734
01:02:02,000 --> 01:02:04,050
I don't know how to thank you.

735
01:02:05,389 --> 01:02:06,777
I'd love a take-away.

736
01:02:08,045 --> 01:02:09,683
Consider it done.

737
01:02:12,112 --> 01:02:13,499
Flying low.

738
01:02:22,479 --> 01:02:25,686
So, Johnny, what are you going to do
about Vortex'?

739
01:02:27,120 --> 01:02:31,604
I don't know. If only Simon was here.
He'd know what to do.

740
01:02:31,667 --> 01:02:34,042
Why do you think he's better than you?

741
01:02:34,639 --> 01:02:36,561
Well, the man's a god.

742
01:02:36,846 --> 01:02:38,765
Well, I prefer mortals.

743
01:02:40,625 --> 01:02:44,149
Pure, complicated, maddening mortals.

744
01:02:45,968 --> 01:02:48,467
I've come to realise
that what's really exciting to me

745
01:02:48,559 --> 01:02:53,393
is great loyalty, determination,
and courage.

746
01:02:54,831 --> 01:02:57,877
You have always fascinated me, clinically.

747
01:02:59,920 --> 01:03:01,555
But now you...

748
01:03:03,280 --> 01:03:07,928
Ms Sumner, your pupils are dilating.

749
01:03:08,306 --> 01:03:10,042
Are they?

750
01:03:11,474 --> 01:03:13,875
Your cheeks are colouring.

751
01:03:14,226 --> 01:03:16,405
Eye contact deepening.

752
01:03:16,752 --> 01:03:18,553
Heart-rate rising.

753
01:03:20,755 --> 01:03:26,483
Ms Sumner,
I believe we're emotionally leaking.

754
01:03:28,307 --> 01:03:29,330
(DOORBELL RINGS)

755
01:03:30,064 --> 01:03:32,793
- The bedroom, quickly.
- Absolutely.

756
01:03:33,423 --> 01:03:34,611
Now!

757
01:03:42,323 --> 01:03:44,220
- Hello?
- [AMBROSE]: Hello.

758
01:03:44,274 --> 01:03:46,520
- Oh, Simon.
- Hi, Kate.

759
01:03:47,087 --> 01:03:49,521
You ready? I'll drive you to the airport.

760
01:03:49,586 --> 01:03:52,117
[SUMNER]: How nice.
I'll just get my bag.

761
01:03:56,881 --> 01:03:58,168
[AMBROSE]: You alone?

762
01:03:58,287 --> 01:03:59,958
(WHISPERING) No.
(LOUDER) Of course.

763
01:04:00,048 --> 01:04:01,172
[AMBROSE]: Been working?

764
01:04:01,232 --> 01:04:04,858
[SUMNER]: Been brushing up
on the Chinese PM. You?

765
01:04:04,915 --> 01:04:06,683
We're trying to track clown Johnny English

766
01:04:10,228 --> 01:04:14,494
There's some questions
we want to ask him, about Vortex.

767
01:04:14,546 --> 01:04:16,116
I don't suppose you've seen him, have you?

768
01:04:16,210 --> 01:04:17,236
No.

769
01:04:18,452 --> 01:04:20,218
Not hiding him away?

770
01:04:21,009 --> 01:04:24,054
Not my type. (CHUCKLES)
Shall we?

771
01:04:24,213 --> 01:04:25,203
Mmm-hmm.

772
01:05:04,722 --> 01:05:06,677
Ambrose.

773
01:05:07,126 --> 01:05:08,792
(VACUUM CLEANER WHIRRING)

774
01:05:34,132 --> 01:05:35,125
(WHIRRING STOPS)

775
01:05:56,532 --> 01:05:57,523
(EXCLAIMS)

776
01:06:01,557 --> 01:06:02,549
(SCREAMS)

777
01:06:06,226 --> 01:06:07,253
(ENGLISH GRUNTING)

778
01:06:36,563 --> 01:06:39,129
There's a Mr Adams to see you, Colin.

779
01:06:40,694 --> 01:06:43,324
- Hello, Tucker.
- What are you doing here?

780
01:06:43,414 --> 01:06:46,207
Every agent in the country is after you.

781
01:06:46,292 --> 01:06:47,645
We were right about Ambrose

782
01:06:48,532 --> 01:06:49,591
What do you mean "we"?

783
01:06:49,683 --> 01:06:50,938
And if we can act fast, we can still...

784
01:06:50,995 --> 01:06:53,178
You wouldn't listen, would you?

785
01:06:53,235 --> 01:06:56,000
You think you know it all. Well' you don't!

786
01:06:56,086 --> 01:06:58,782
Being an agent means everything to me.

787
01:06:58,838 --> 01:07:01,021
And, thanks to you, I'm suspended!

788
01:07:02,322 --> 01:07:04,280
Would you boys like some orange squash?

789
01:07:04,373 --> 01:07:06,175
- No, thank you.
- Bye, thanks, Mum.

790
01:07:08,215 --> 01:07:13,345
Tucker, Ambrose is in Switzerland.
We are in Tooting.

791
01:07:14,359 --> 01:07:17,368
I am here because my country needs me.

792
01:07:19,316 --> 01:07:22,459
And because it needs you, too.

793
01:07:40,917 --> 01:07:43,515
<i>- Royce.
- [AUTOMATED VOICE]: Ready, sir.</i>

794
01:07:44,148 --> 01:07:45,568
Come.

795
01:07:50,772 --> 01:07:52,312
<i>[AUTOMATED VOICE]:
Obstruction detected.</i>

796
01:07:53,813 --> 01:07:54,808
(ALARM BLARING)

797
01:08:11,575 --> 01:08:14,846
Set the sat nav for Switzerland
Let's kick some bottom.

798
01:08:45,590 --> 01:08:48,703
<i>[AUTOMATED VOICE]:
You have arrived at your destination.</i>

799
01:08:49,721 --> 01:08:51,422
<i>Good luck, sir!</i>

800
01:08:59,640 --> 01:09:04,539
Le Bastion. One way up, one way down.

801
01:09:07,642 --> 01:09:09,538
Come on. Let's get the stuff.

802
01:09:14,293 --> 01:09:17,920
Whoa, look. The T-2 ground-to-air missile!

803
01:09:18,935 --> 01:09:21,502
That's a D-7 bulletproof shield.

804
01:09:21,753 --> 01:09:23,355
Take it from me, Tucker.

805
01:09:23,446 --> 01:09:26,208
I was working with these
while you were stringing conkers.

806
01:09:26,392 --> 01:09:27,929
(CHATTERING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

807
01:09:55,095 --> 01:09:56,481
The P-8 grapple hook?

808
01:09:57,593 --> 01:09:58,782
Check.

809
01:09:58,839 --> 01:10:00,477
- [ENGLISH]: Estimated height?
- Thirty-five feet.

810
01:10:00,567 --> 01:10:02,009
All yours, Tucker.

811
01:10:02,072 --> 01:10:03,841
Can I just say, sir'?

812
01:10:05,559 --> 01:10:07,609
This is just great.

813
01:10:10,072 --> 01:10:11,807
Well, go on.

814
01:10:19,450 --> 01:10:22,241
The D-16 ascender, and up we go.

815
01:10:23,096 --> 01:10:24,569
Are you sure that's the ascender, sir?

816
01:10:24,634 --> 01:10:26,171
Yes, yes, I'd know it anywhere.

817
01:10:26,840 --> 01:10:29,853
<i>[AUTOMATED VOICE]:
Agent in distress. Agent in distress.</i>

818
01:10:29,915 --> 01:10:31,932
(ALARM BLARING)

819
01:10:35,353 --> 01:10:36,377
(INDISTINCT)

820
01:10:36,889 --> 01:10:37,880
(DOG BARKING)

821
01:10:38,776 --> 01:10:42,719
<i>Agent in distress. Agent in distress.</i>

822
01:10:45,370 --> 01:10:47,006
<i>I am over here!</i>

823
01:10:47,097 --> 01:10:48,766
Shut up! Shut up!

824
01:10:48,855 --> 01:10:50,622
<i>I am over here!</i>

825
01:10:57,082 --> 01:10:58,074
(SIREN STOPS)

826
01:11:00,123 --> 01:11:02,783
<i>[MUFFLED AUTOMATED VOICE]:
Activating visual locator.</i>

827
01:11:02,841 --> 01:11:06,169
<i>Three, two, one.</i>

828
01:11:08,856 --> 01:11:09,852
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

829
01:11:12,891 --> 01:11:14,462
<i>[MAN ON LOUDSPEAKERS]:
Intruders in Sector Four!</i>

830
01:11:14,876 --> 01:11:16,958
(MAN ANNOUNCING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

831
01:11:17,208 --> 01:11:18,201
(DOGS BARKING)

832
01:11:20,859 --> 01:11:24,318
Dear God, let me not die
at the hands of the Swiss.

833
01:11:25,689 --> 01:11:28,770
Tucker, now listen. I want you to attack me

834
01:11:28,859 --> 01:11:30,394
- What?
- After a struggle,

835
01:11:30,487 --> 01:11:34,145
you can "arrest me"
and take me inside as your prisoner.

836
01:11:34,200 --> 01:11:36,634
- Sir, I can't.
- Tucker, that's an order.

837
01:11:37,916 --> 01:11:40,261
Hit me. Hit me.

838
01:11:42,044 --> 01:11:43,485
Come on, harder.

839
01:11:44,377 --> 01:11:47,171
- Better, sh'?
- (GRUNTING) Yes, much better.

840
01:11:49,724 --> 01:11:51,619
I can see how people get a taste for this.

841
01:11:54,009 --> 01:11:56,228
I got a better idea. I'll shoot you!

842
01:11:56,285 --> 01:11:57,888
No, no, no.

843
01:11:58,013 --> 01:11:59,929
- Die, Vortex scum!
- Tucker!

844
01:12:01,721 --> 01:12:03,422
(AGENTS SHOUTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

845
01:12:05,562 --> 01:12:07,039
Agent Tucker!

846
01:12:10,363 --> 01:12:11,805
It's Johnny English.

847
01:12:14,490 --> 01:12:15,963
Bag him.

848
01:12:31,993 --> 01:12:33,827
[AMBROSE]: The glass can withstand
mortar attack.

849
01:12:34,206 --> 01:12:37,032
The door's one-way.
You can get out, but no one gets in.

850
01:12:37,084 --> 01:12:38,339
Excellent.

851
01:12:42,810 --> 01:12:44,482
You ready, Slater'?

852
01:12:51,420 --> 01:12:53,505
I'll have them send refreshments
to your room

853
01:12:53,565 --> 01:12:54,720
when you're ready, Pegasus.

854
01:12:54,812 --> 01:12:56,316
Thank you, Agent One.

855
01:13:05,342 --> 01:13:07,326
I'll take it from here, boys.

856
01:13:09,916 --> 01:13:11,683
Hold it right there!

857
01:13:13,564 --> 01:13:15,299
Let me see your ID.

858
01:13:16,572 --> 01:13:18,405
- [ENGLISH WHISPERING]: Excuse me
- What the...

859
01:13:21,693 --> 01:13:22,849
Stop!

860
01:13:24,058 --> 01:13:26,886
Warning,
this is a designated conflict zone.

861
01:13:29,048 --> 01:13:30,624
(GRUNTING)

862
01:13:31,968 --> 01:13:32,958
(CHUCKLES)

863
01:13:35,101 --> 01:13:37,663
Sir'? Sir?

864
01:13:44,923 --> 01:13:46,790
(MEN CHATTERING)

865
01:13:52,475 --> 01:13:53,502
(GRUNTS)

866
01:13:54,395 --> 01:13:57,123
- [PEGASUS]: Thank you so much
- You're welcome, Pegasus.

867
01:13:57,755 --> 01:13:59,013
[ENGLISH]: Pegasus.

868
01:14:07,738 --> 01:14:11,428
Go on. Go on.

869
01:14:16,573 --> 01:14:17,565
(GASPS)

870
01:14:18,877 --> 01:14:20,131
What the hell is that?

871
01:14:26,461 --> 01:14:29,541
Sir'? Sir?

872
01:14:32,127 --> 01:14:33,381
- English!
- Pegasus.

873
01:14:34,684 --> 01:14:37,033
They're going to make you kill Xiang Ping!

874
01:14:37,087 --> 01:14:38,341
You're insane!

875
01:14:41,277 --> 01:14:42,979
Agent One, thank God.

876
01:14:43,293 --> 01:14:48,260
He won't help you.
He's the third member of Vortex.

877
01:14:48,317 --> 01:14:50,214
Aren't you, Simon?

878
01:14:52,635 --> 01:14:56,263
Here to give you some Timoxy bubby...

879
01:14:56,320 --> 01:14:58,218
(STUTTERING) Timoxy bubby

880
01:14:59,807 --> 01:15:02,404
Timoxy bubby...

881
01:15:04,539 --> 01:15:09,572
To give you a drug that will make you
obey his every command.

882
01:15:17,820 --> 01:15:19,590
I'm intrigued, Simon.

883
01:15:20,956 --> 01:15:24,932
How exactly
were you going to administer it?

884
01:15:29,600 --> 01:15:31,169
By injection?

885
01:15:36,000 --> 01:15:39,360
Some hideous gas through the air vents?

886
01:15:45,438 --> 01:15:47,749
Or by spiking her drink?

887
01:15:50,204 --> 01:15:52,227
Timoxeline Barbebutenol.

888
01:15:57,440 --> 01:16:01,574
He'll enter the manic phase
any moment now.

889
01:16:02,718 --> 01:16:05,664
(SCOFFS) I have to warn you that I've been
trained to resist this kind of thing.

890
01:16:05,888 --> 01:16:07,591
(STUTTERING)

891
01:16:09,089 --> 01:16:10,791
You swine.

892
01:16:11,903 --> 01:16:13,506
Agent One, what's going on?

893
01:16:13,565 --> 01:16:16,068
He's quite harmless at this phase.

894
01:16:16,127 --> 01:16:18,307
The drug will kill him,
but just before it does,

895
01:16:18,397 --> 01:16:21,575
there'll be a short window
where he'll do everything I tell him to.

896
01:16:29,565 --> 01:16:30,627
Poor Johnny.

897
01:16:31,905 --> 01:16:33,573
You were never really Ml-7, Johnny.

898
01:16:33,665 --> 01:16:35,811
You were never really one of us.

899
01:16:35,905 --> 01:16:39,114
Now you're about to become
our most famous agent.

900
01:16:46,942 --> 01:16:50,306
You'll now do exactly as I tell you.

901
01:16:50,370 --> 01:16:53,033
You are a traitor to the Service
and to your country.

902
01:16:53,089 --> 01:16:54,564
Shut her up, old chap.

903
01:16:56,001 --> 01:16:58,149
- Duck.
- What?

904
01:17:00,864 --> 01:17:02,306
I warned you.

905
01:17:03,200 --> 01:17:05,667
Okay, Slater. Let's get him ready.

906
01:17:08,545 --> 01:17:09,833
Ready.

907
01:17:10,622 --> 01:17:13,452
[PRIME MINISTER]: Premier Ping,
it's a pleasure to finally meet you.

908
01:17:13,825 --> 01:17:16,137
You had a pleasant flight, I trust?

909
01:17:16,543 --> 01:17:19,426
I was just asking the Premier
if he had a pleasant flight.

910
01:17:21,826 --> 01:17:24,223
Kate, Johnny's back on the team.

911
01:17:24,319 --> 01:17:25,574
What?

912
01:17:25,662 --> 01:17:28,131
It's all checked out and the PM
and the Chinese have approved it.

913
01:17:28,225 --> 01:17:30,058
- Approved what?
- He's standing in for Pamela.

914
01:17:30,146 --> 01:17:32,128
Isn't it great?

915
01:17:41,280 --> 01:17:45,450
Excuse me. Agent Tucker.

916
01:17:50,787 --> 01:17:53,728
[PRIME MINISTER]: Good, good.
And your wife is well?

917
01:17:54,463 --> 01:17:56,330
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)

918
01:17:57,824 --> 01:18:00,391
<i>[AMBROSE]: Lock it up, Johnny.</i>

919
01:18:00,482 --> 01:18:01,835
[PRIME MINISTER]: Wonderful.

920
01:18:03,426 --> 01:18:04,780
<i>[AMBROSE]: That's it.</i>

921
01:18:13,891 --> 01:18:18,245
Premier, I am most grateful you have
agreed to meet me at this time.

922
01:18:19,267 --> 01:18:21,663
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)

923
01:18:24,769 --> 01:18:26,538
It is our pleasure.

924
01:18:27,427 --> 01:18:28,614
Maintain that tone, Prime Minister.

925
01:18:28,705 --> 01:18:30,408
Avoid confrontation, keep eye contact.

926
01:18:31,745 --> 01:18:33,996
I can assure you that the Chinese people

927
01:18:34,083 --> 01:18:38,883
have always regarded the British
people as completely horrible.

928
01:18:40,704 --> 01:18:42,539
- Honourable.
- Honourable.

929
01:18:43,525 --> 01:18:45,835
Completely honourable.

930
01:18:46,628 --> 01:18:47,982
Of course.

931
01:18:49,571 --> 01:18:51,437
I was very keen to meet...

932
01:18:59,203 --> 01:19:00,973
(SWISHING)

933
01:19:08,962 --> 01:19:11,758
Johnny, stand up and go to the water table.

934
01:19:17,506 --> 01:19:19,907
[PRIME MINISTER]: Premier,
I believe the present danger

935
01:19:20,005 --> 01:19:21,673
can be averted if we act swiftly.

936
01:19:21,764 --> 01:19:23,748
Go to your right pocket.

937
01:19:27,267 --> 01:19:29,255
We designed it for Pegasus.

938
01:19:29,348 --> 01:19:31,911
Well, it's too bloody late now.

939
01:19:35,426 --> 01:19:36,484
Just act natural.

940
01:19:43,812 --> 01:19:44,805
(SIGHS)

941
01:19:49,762 --> 01:19:51,816
- Prime Minister, traditionally...
- Somethings wrong.

942
01:19:51,909 --> 01:19:54,373
...China does not respond well to advice...

943
01:19:54,467 --> 01:19:56,073
Pull out the barrel.

944
01:19:58,627 --> 01:20:01,834
Now, Johnny, I want you to kill Xiang Ping.

945
01:20:04,962 --> 01:20:06,731
Oh, dear God, no.

946
01:20:09,350 --> 01:20:10,701
He's being controlled.

947
01:20:10,787 --> 01:20:12,174
[FOREIGN SECRETARY]: By who?

948
01:20:12,772 --> 01:20:14,058
[TUCKER]: Ambrose.

949
01:20:15,108 --> 01:20:16,428
Shoot Xiang Ping!

950
01:20:20,868 --> 01:20:25,035
Mind must be master of the body.

951
01:20:28,228 --> 01:20:29,995
[AMBROSE]: He's resisting it.

952
01:20:31,267 --> 01:20:34,311
His left hand is fighting the right hand.

953
01:20:38,885 --> 01:20:40,392
Come on, Johnny.

954
01:20:41,382 --> 01:20:42,798
[TUCKER]:
If I can interrupt the frequency,

955
01:20:42,884 --> 01:20:44,749
I could stop Ambrose
from communicating with him.

956
01:20:45,027 --> 01:20:46,021
(GRUNTS)

957
01:21:01,507 --> 01:21:03,144
English, stand up!

958
01:21:13,028 --> 01:21:14,153
[TUCKER]: Come on
Come on.

959
01:21:17,444 --> 01:21:19,146
He'll be dead in 50 seconds, sir.

960
01:21:21,830 --> 01:21:22,987
Tucker!

961
01:21:23,751 --> 01:21:24,872
Come on.

962
01:21:25,828 --> 01:21:27,532
- Pull the trigger!
- [TUCKER]: I'm in.

963
01:21:27,750 --> 01:21:29,766
(DANCE MUSIC BLARING)

964
01:21:44,101 --> 01:21:45,607
(RADIO STATIC)

965
01:21:45,702 --> 01:21:46,727
(MUSIC STOPS)

966
01:21:47,751 --> 01:21:49,617
Listen to me, this is Simon Ambrose,

967
01:21:49,703 --> 01:21:52,396
<i>(ON INTERCOM) and I order you
to shoot Xiang Ping!</i>

968
01:21:56,101 --> 01:21:57,191
Ten seconds, sir.

969
01:21:59,588 --> 01:22:00,749
Fire!

970
01:22:07,461 --> 01:22:08,487
(GRUNTING)

971
01:22:11,047 --> 01:22:12,620
Go, go, go.

972
01:22:12,712 --> 01:22:14,662
Time to get out of here.

973
01:22:18,953 --> 01:22:20,240
Hold your fire!

974
01:22:21,190 --> 01:22:22,574
Stand down!

975
01:22:34,952 --> 01:22:36,652
(HEART MONITOR BEEPING)

976
01:22:47,111 --> 01:22:48,170
His pulse is dropping.

977
01:22:48,262 --> 01:22:49,614
Don't lose him!

978
01:22:49,700 --> 01:22:51,121
Come on, sir.

979
01:23:33,192 --> 01:23:38,254
<i>[WANG]: Open your head, English,
and you shall be reborn.</i>

980
01:23:50,791 --> 01:23:52,329
Almost there.

981
01:24:19,909 --> 01:24:21,452
Thank you, Kate.

982
01:24:21,546 --> 01:24:22,802
I was passing.

983
01:24:23,434 --> 01:24:24,754
[TUCKER]: Sir.

984
01:24:24,873 --> 01:24:26,160
Tucker!

985
01:24:27,371 --> 01:24:28,721
Welcome back, sir.

986
01:24:29,033 --> 01:24:30,057
Thank you, Tucker.

987
01:24:30,153 --> 01:24:31,473
I won't kiss you, if you don't mind.

988
01:24:31,592 --> 01:24:33,198
Well, whatever.

989
01:24:37,035 --> 01:24:38,158
Where's Ambrose?

990
01:24:49,609 --> 01:24:51,150
English?

991
01:24:51,276 --> 01:24:53,390
Sir. What are you doing, sir'?

992
01:24:53,514 --> 01:24:57,714
Guideline 17-5: Never question
a senior agent in the field.

993
01:24:57,830 --> 01:24:58,987
No!

994
01:26:35,628 --> 01:26:38,485
Ambrose' you five-star turd.

995
01:26:38,636 --> 01:26:39,627
(AMBROSE GRUNTS)

996
01:26:45,038 --> 01:26:46,867
(BOTH GRUNTING)

997
01:27:02,348 --> 01:27:04,399
Another balls-up, Johnny.

998
01:27:12,877 --> 01:27:13,838
Ooh.

999
01:27:15,630 --> 01:27:17,201
What's the matter with you?

1000
01:27:19,308 --> 01:27:20,298
(YAWNING)

1001
01:27:36,941 --> 01:27:38,642
(GRUNTING)

1002
01:27:40,269 --> 01:27:41,842
It's all over, Ambrose.

1003
01:27:43,438 --> 01:27:47,791
You can betray your country,
you can cheat your friends,

1004
01:27:47,915 --> 01:27:51,279
but you can't get away
from Johnny English...

1005
01:27:51,630 --> 01:27:52,622
(SCREAMING)

1006
01:27:55,180 --> 01:27:56,720
(GRUNTING)

1007
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:08,889
So long, Johnny!

1008
01:28:10,861 --> 01:28:11,920
(GUNSHOT)

1009
01:28:14,988 --> 01:28:16,307
The D-7.

1010
01:28:17,196 --> 01:28:19,280
The bulletproof shield!

1011
01:28:20,781 --> 01:28:23,181
Hey! It's not working!

1012
01:28:23,598 --> 01:28:25,552
It's the T-2, sir!

1013
01:28:25,679 --> 01:28:28,274
- Is he... Oh, he's alive!
- It's the T-2!

1014
01:28:28,718 --> 01:28:30,832
Close it. Close ii!

1015
01:28:30,956 --> 01:28:32,562
Stupid thing!

1016
01:28:45,259 --> 01:28:46,680
Oh, Johnny.

1017
01:28:52,077 --> 01:28:53,431
The T-2.

1018
01:28:57,199 --> 01:29:00,470
Tucker, you clever boy.

1019
01:29:20,079 --> 01:29:21,269
[PRIME MINISTER]:
I couldn't be more delighted.

1020
01:29:21,360 --> 01:29:23,348
Vortex's paymasters have been arrested,

1021
01:29:23,441 --> 01:29:27,124
and China has expressed its gratitude
to both Britain and the Service.

1022
01:29:28,558 --> 01:29:30,031
We owe English a great deal.

1023
01:29:34,161 --> 01:29:37,400
Well, reinstating his knighthood
is a truly lovely gesture.

1024
01:29:37,521 --> 01:29:38,841
And it will mean the world to him.

1025
01:29:41,196 --> 01:29:43,153
Her Majesty will be with him shortly.

1026
01:30:10,638 --> 01:30:11,631
(SCREAMING)

1027
01:30:26,991 --> 01:30:29,042
Gotcha! Gotcha.

1028
01:30:40,785 --> 01:30:42,074
Got you!

1029
01:30:45,038 --> 01:30:48,119
[ENGLISH]: Just about
had enough of you, you old cow!

1030
01:30:48,176 --> 01:30:51,000
You're going nowhere! Pegasus!

1031
01:30:51,055 --> 01:30:52,112
English!

1032
01:30:52,175 --> 01:30:56,311
It's her! It's the killer cleaner!
Finally, I've got her!

1033
01:30:58,737 --> 01:31:01,682
You never know when it's over, do you?

1034
01:31:01,743 --> 01:31:06,424
Well, it's over, over, over, over, over!

1035
01:31:26,418 --> 01:31:28,024
(SLOW SONG PLAYING)

1036
01:34:32,114 --> 01:34:33,851
I don't know how to thank you.

1037
01:34:33,907 --> 01:34:35,385
I'd love a take-away.

1038
01:34:36,725 --> 01:34:38,970
Consider it done.

1039
01:34:58,069 --> 01:34:59,608
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

